gomodel:SYNGO_213  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: This paper describes immuno-EM data demonstrating that in hippocampus and cerebellum of rats, mGluR1 is preferentially localized at the periphery of the postsynaptic density.\n\n24/2/2017 Pim\n\"integral component ...\" term derived from TM domains in protein.. Experimental description: from M&M:\nPreparation of Animals and Tissue\nTen adult female or male rats (100-400g) were deeply anesthetized with sodium pentobarbital(150\nmg/kg,i.p.). They were per-fused through the aorta with NaCl solution (O.Y%, 1 min) followed by ice-cold fixative containing 4%paraformaldehyde, 0.025%-0.1% glutaraldehyde, and approximately0.2% picricacid (Somogyi and Takagi, 1982) made up in 0.1 M phosphate buffer (PB, pH7.2), for 10-30 min." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_213" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

